# Validation loop

Run the smallest check that proves the change. Do not claim success without command output.

## C# mod (primary)

Requires **`lib/`** (run **`setup-lib.ps1 -GamePath "<STS2 install>"`** once) and **.NET 9 SDK**.

```powershell
dotnet build .\Sts2ContextCoach.csproj -c Release
dotnet test .\Sts2ContextCoach.Tests\Sts2ContextCoach.Tests.csproj -c Release
```

- Keep new **Data/** ingestion testable without Godot logging (`Diagnostics/CoachGameLog` pattern).
- Avoid calling **`MegaCrit.Sts2.Core.Logging.Log`** from code paths hit by xUnit.

## Python tools (when touching `tools/`)

From repo root with **`sts2-context-coach`** conda env (see **`README.md`**):

```powershell
ruff format .
ruff check .
set PYTHONPATH=.
python -m unittest discover -s tools/run_insights/tests -p "test_*.py" -v
python -m unittest discover -s tools/data_refresh/tests -p "test_*.py" -v
```

## Release zip (release changes only)

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\tools\release\build-release.ps1
```

## Safety (never break)

- Runtime mod must work **without LLM** (`scoring_mode=heuristic`).
- Do **not** commit secrets: **`local.props`**, **`tools/data_refresh/config.yaml`**, API keys.
- **`data_refresh`** must not silently overwrite curated **`Data/*.json`** — use review/apply flow.
- Shipped metadata stays **embedded in the DLL** for production; loose JSON under mod folders breaks STS2 mod scanning.
